Deploying a image stored in dockerhub on kubernetes cluster using minikube

->Install and Setup Minikube
	*Goto official minikube website and find the commands for installation
	*curl -LO https://github.com/kubernetes/minikube/releases/latest/download/minikube-linux-amd64
	*sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube && rm minikube-linux-amd64
	
->Initialize and start kubernetes environment 
	*minikube start
	
->Install kubectl and verify
	*sudo snap install kubectl --classic
	*kubectl version
	*kubectl cluster info
	
->Authenticate with dockerhub credentials
	*eval $(minikube docker-env)
	*docker login
	
->Deploy the application and expose the port at which it is running
	*kubectl create deployment <app-name> --image=<docker_hub_username>/<docker_hub_repo_name>:<tagname>
	*kubectl expose deployment <app-name> --type=NodePort --port=<port_in_which_app_runs>
	
->After a minute or two, you can view your deployment
	*minikube service <app-name>
	*This gives the URL where the app is running and opens up browser showing the response
	
->Delete Deployment and service
	*kubectl delete deployment <app-name>
	*kubectl delete service <app-name>
	
->stop minikube
	*minikube start


